This paper discusses a modelling method based on workflows, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). It also mentions the Workflow Management Coalition Terminology and Glossary, which is related to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC) as workflows are often used in these areas. Finally, the paper may be of interest to the programming languages community (cs.PL) as it discusses executable models.
